etymologies: mid 19th century (in an earlier sense). From ret- (in ancient Greek ῥητίνη resin) + -ene

definitions: A crystalline aromatic hydrocarbon occurring in coal tar and as a product of the breakdown of conifer resins.

notes.text: Retene has a tricyclic molecule based on a phenanthrene ring system. Systematic name: 1-methyl-7-isopropylphenanthrene; C₁₈H₁₈.
